Good afternoon,

We want to update you on the current situation. As of today, we remain at Orange Level II. Last week we were at 27.27 and this week we are at 42.43. This activates our A/B schedule that we outlined in our video last week. Please watch this week’s video to learn more about the A/B schedule. You should also have received distance learning guidelines this week from your child’s principal. Please notify the school if you did not receive those.

Moving Forward Together,

Nick Highsmith
Superintendent
Welch Public Schools

post_text:
COVID-19 Update

On Friday, Craig County moved to the orange level according to the Oklahoma State Department of Health COVID-19 risk map. (Found here: https://coronavirus.health.ok.gov/covid-19-alert-system). We are at Orange Level 1 according to our Return to Learn Plan. We are at the lower end of Orange Level 1 and will continue with the safety protocols that we have already been using (masks when you cannot socially distance, no visitors, etc.).

We will continue to monitor the situation. If we continue to climb in the orange category we may have to move to an alternative (A/B) schedule. Our team has that schedule figured out and will send more information out IF we climb higher in the orange category in future weeks. The color coded map is updated every Friday.

We have had a great first full week and we are looking forward to great 2020-2021 school year!

Moving Forward Together,

WPS Administrative Team

Open House “Wildcat Welcome” is TODAY.

We have staggered times to help reduce congestion. If you cannot make it during your time, please contact the school about an alternative time.

The Welch Public Schools Enrichment Foundation is hosting a hamburger/hotdog feed to the west of the old gym (field). This is a fundraiser to help the foundation after they purchased new computers for every teacher.

All adult visitors will be required to wear a face covering when in the building. Teachers will be stationed at their classrooms to meet students, pass out any papers, and take student items.

Online enrollment assistance will be offered in the cafeteria.

post_text:
Dear Prom Parents & Spectators:

As we make final preparations for prom, we wanted to inform everyone that we are taking health precautions and following social distancing guidelines to protect students, parents, grandparents, and spectators. We want to protect everyone from any unnecessary exposures. We will not be having our traditional walk in ceremony to minimize crowds and promote social distancing. Only students that are attending prom will be allowed inside the prom venue on Thursday night. We will have someone doing a virtual broadcast at the venue building so everyone can see the students all dressed up. People are welcome to watch students as they arrive at the venue from the parking lot and the venue path entrance. We ask that everyone promote social distancing and be respectful of others as we provide a safe environment for our students.
Thank you for your understanding.

post_text:
Oklahoma’s Promise: Alert for 10th-Grade Parents With Recent Income Loss

https://www.okhighered.org/okpromise/



If your student is or was in the 10th grade during the 2019-20 school year and you anticipate that your 2020 income may be under the $55,000 application limit for the Oklahoma’s Promise scholarship due to recent reductions in your income, you may submit an application based on your 2020 estimated income. The application must be submitted prior to the June 30, 2020, deadline. You will be required to provide a copy of your 2020 federal tax return when completed to verify that your 2020 income was under $55,000. The application will be held as pending until the tax documentation is received. Please send any questions to okpromise@osrhe.edu

post_text:
Parents and Students,

Hopefully, this finds you happy and healthy. The pandemic and subsequent school closure have caused hardships for many and a nontraditional education for our students. In March, before rolling out a distance learning plan, Welch Public School concentrated on student and family needs, taking care of faculty and staff, and how we could facilitate learning from a distance. There was no ‘playbook’ for addressing a school closure, but our faculty and staff performed admirably to shift to a distance learning model quickly. With the uncertainty of what school will look like next year, we would like your feedback to help us make decisions regarding what will be best for WPS students during the 2020-21 school year. Please complete the survey below.

Thank you,
Welch Administrative Team

https://forms.gle/g27e5EfSE9hke9iF9

Welch Elementary School will be hosting a drive through awards assembly on Tuesday, May 12. Each grade has a specific time to line up in their cars and pull through the circle drive in front of the high school. Teachers will then hand out awards to each student, in their car, as they parade through the circle drive. We ask that you follow the times listed for each grade.
PK - 9:00
K- 9:45
1st - 10:30
2nd - 11:15
3rd - 1:00
4th - 1:45
5th - 2:30
We miss our students and want a chance to award them for their accomplishments. We also want to see our students one more time before summer. We hope everyone can attend.

FRIDAY NIGHT LIGHTS AT WELCH PUBLIC SCHOOLS
IN HONOR OF THE CLASS OF 2020

Tonight, Friday, April 10th, we will join schools around the country by turning our stadium lights on for Friday Night Lights and leaving them lit for 20 minutes, and 20 seconds to honor this year's Senior Class of 2020.

At 8:20 p.m. tonight, drive-by our sports fields to see the glow of the lights, and show support for our graduating class of 2020. Sound your horns, and cheer loudly for our seniors!

Please stay in your vehicles and follow CDC guidance on COVID -19. Stay healthy, and stay safe.

Proud to be a Wildcat!

post_text:
Welch High School is proud to join the nationwide campaign on Friday to honor the 2020 Senior Class!

High schools around Oklahoma and across the country are banding together to honor the 2020 senior class amidst the coronavirus pandemic.

On Friday, April 10, at 8:20 p.m., Welch High School baseball field, softball field, and outdoor stadiums around the state and country will turn on their lights for 20 minutes to show their appreciation for the senior class, families, coaches and athletes as part of the “Be the Light” campaign.

The lights are a beacon to show the Senior Class we are thinking of them and to remind them there will be a time where we will be all together once again.

The “Be the Light” campaign has been spreading across the nation as schools look for a way to celebrate their graduating seniors who are having their final memories in high school stripped away due to the outbreak.

Proud to be a Wildcat!

Welch High School Administrative Team and Athletic Department

Take care students, we miss you! We are here for you if you need us.

post_text: Our speech therapists provide some fun ideas to help younger students! 🗣🗯💙
shared_text:
Phonemic Awareness Outdoor Activities by Royalty Speech Therapy

Royalty Speech Therapy is at Royalty Speech Therapy.
March 26 at 4:26 PM · Miami, OK ·

Check out our how-to video on teaching phonemic awareness to your kids at home! Phonemic awareness skills such as phoneme isolation, segmentation, blending, and manipulation build into later phonological skills such as rhyming and syllable structure of words.

These are our basic foundational skills for literacy development!

We know stress is high for parents at home working with their kids and switching to distance learning, so we hope little activities like these can help! We will be posting a how to video every couple of days of language based activities. Reach out to us if you want us to cover something specific or even if you have any questions! We’re here to help our community as much as possible during this time! 🖤👑

post_text:
Important information for all students:
Starting tomorrow meals for 18 year olds and younger can be picked up at cafeteria outside the elementary doors. These meals are free to all children 18 years of age and younger. Each child will receive two meals in one bag, a breakfast and a lunch. We ask that everyone please stay in vehicles and grab the meals off the cart as they pull through the circle drive.

Families that receive backpack items daily may pick up supplies for the week Monday, March 23 from 10 to 11 at the elementary doors through the circle drive.

No one will be allowed in the building to pick up meals or backpack items. Everyone should stay in their vehicles.

Medications and any essential items students may need can be picked up at the appropriate offices. Parents, please call ahead and we will have medication and items ready for parents at the door.

The WPS administration and staff are here for our students and their families if anyone needs anything during the next two weeks. Please call the school between 9 and 3 daily.

post_text: We want to inform you that the State Board of Education has enacted a mandatory shut down of all public schools until April 6th. The mandated closure includes all activities, practices, and all school-sponsored events. The administrative team will be meeting this week to make plans for the upcoming weeks. As we gain more information from the State Department we will plan accordingly. This situation is unprecedented and continues to evolve by the hour. We want to assure you Welch Public School is doing everything possible to ensure the needs of our students and employees will be met during this time of uncertainty. Stay safe and enjoy your time with family. We encourage our students and staff to follow healthy hygiene habits and social distancing information provided by the Oklahoma State Department of Health, the Oklahoma Department of education, and the Centers for Disease Control. The health and safety of our students, staff, and community will be the focus of our decisions. Thank you for your flexibility and understanding during this unusual event. WILDCAT PRIDE!

post_text: Welch BPA was very successful at the State Leadership Conference in Tulsa. Welch has two state winners & five “top 8” medalists: Justin Haskell - 2nd Advanced Spreadsheets, Rachel Rife - 3rd Integrated Office Applications. Top 8: Corinthian Bowin, Jaci Clinton in Advanced Spreadsheets; Gage Miller in Personal Financial Management ; Emoree Bradbury in Fundamentals of Spreadsheets; Rachel Rife in Administrative Support Concepts, Business Meeting Management Concepts & Management, Marketing & HR Concepts. Emoree was also named a recipient of the Gina Hubbard BPA Scholarship. Rachel & Austin served as voting delegates for the Welch chapter. Justin & Rachel now qualify for the National Conference in Washington DC in May.

shared_text:
Precollegiate Programs at OU
February 25 at 3:50 PM ·

In partnership with the Oklahoma State Regents for Higher Education, we are so excited to be able to offer three week-long FREE residential summer camps to Oklahoma students this summer! Applications can be downloaded at youth.ou.edu

We are partnering with the Christopher C. Gibbs College of Architecture at the University of Oklahoma, the Oklahoma Mesonet, and the University of Oklahoma School of Geosciences to bring Oklahoma middle and high school students on campus for a hands-on, week long experience in either Architecture, Meteorology, and Geology.

Find out more information and download applications at youth.ou.edu today! #oklaed #yOUth #summercamps #STEM #geology #meterology #architecture

post_text:
Welch Elementary Math and Literacy Night is tonight from 5:30 to 7:30. All elementary students and parents are encouraged to come participate in a night of fun math and reading activities. Hot dogs will also be served!

Game: There will be 10 turkeys hidden throughout the school. Each student that finds one will receive a 10 to 12lb turkey to take home for Thanksgiving! (Only one per child.) There will also be one Thanksgiving basket filled with all the goodies you will need for a Thanksgiving Dinner, including a turkey, given away at the end of the event.

We would like to thank Shawn and Heather Wiegand from The Cow for the donation of the turkeys and OPPA for the hotdogs and sides.

We hope to see everyone there tonight!

Welch PTO will be having a Craft Fair and Chili Cook Off on November 16 at the Welch Civic Center. If you are interested in having a booth or participating in the chili cook off, please contact the Welch Elementary Office at 918-788-3129. All funds raised will go to support Welch Public School Students.

We would also like to invite everyone to come out on November 16 and visit the craft booths and take part in judging the chili cook off.

post_text: 5th graders have been very busy this month! They’ve practice writing a persuasive essay on why you should buy a haunted house. They learned about our skeleton system by making skeletons out of q-tips, and learned 14 bones with a rap song. They tried to decide what Mrs. Haraughty should be for Halloween, and finally they decorated pumpkins as their favorite book characters! We have had a fun month!

Red Ribbon week activities for middle and high school:
Wed 10/23- red white and blue- United we stand against drugs
Thursday- anti bullying- leave a note on a locker telling that person one great thing you notice about them
Fri- team up against drugs, wear school colors and make an anti drug poster for a prize
Monday- I have a bright future without drugs, wear bright clothes
Tuesday- sock it to drugs- wear crazy socks..also, write a note to a teacher/staff member telling them why you appreciate them
Wednesday- wear red! post something positive on social media about our school! Remember, bully prevention starts with KINDNESS!!!

post_text:
On the first Monday of each month, Elementary Teachers are available from 7:30-8:00 in the elementary lounge for what we like to call “Teacher Talk”. This is just a quick opportunity to touch base with your child’s teacher. Directly following, parents and/or guardians are welcome to attend our weekly Rise&Shine ceremony! Today was the first day for this new event! If you missed it don’t worry, just mark your calendars for November 4th...we look forward to seeing you next time!

P.S. there is coffee and pastries as well 😉
